As shown in Fig. 6D, the fluorescence intensity of the reaction system demonstrated a significant linear correlation with FA concentrations in the range of 0–100 μM. The Stern-Volmer quenching constant (KSV
                        ) was calculated to be 4271.04 L·mol−1, indicating a high binding efficiency between FA and L-CQDs. Linear regression analysis yielded the equation F/F0 =  − 0.0063C(FA) + 0.9929, with a correlation coefficient (R2
                        ) of 0.9961 (Fig. 6E). The limit of detection (LOD) for FA was determined to be 0.27 μM.
